  "prompt": "Luis Von Ahn: What is the current business model of Duolingo?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Duolingo's business model primarily includes a combination of freemium services and premium subscriptions.\n\n1. **Freemium Model**: Duolingo offers free access to its core language learning platform. Users can access various language courses, exercises, and features without any cost. The app generates revenue through ads displayed to these free users.\n\n2. **Subscription (Duolingo Plus)**: Duolingo also offers a premium subscription service known as Duolingo Plus which provides a range of added benefits. These benefits typically include:\n   - An ad-free experience\n   - Offline access to lessons\n   - Progress tracking and enhanced learning insights\n   - Additional features like unlimited hearts, which allow users to make mistakes without being penalized.\n\n3. **In-App Purchases**: Users can make in-app purchases to obtain additional features, like extra hearts or streak freezes to maintain their daily practice streak.\n\nAdditionally, Duolingo has been expanding into other educational areas such as literacy with its Duolingo ABC app, and it launched the Duolingo English Test, which generates revenue through fees for test-takers. These efforts diversify the income streams beyond the core language learning app.\n\nOverall, Duolingo's business model leverages its large user base, offering free content while enticing users to upgrade to the premium subscription for enhanced features and experience.",
